                  <li><b>Faulty Thermostats: </b>A malfunctioning thermostat can lead to inconsistent heating cycles and uneven warm air distribution. Whether it's a simple recalibration or a complete replacement, our HVAC technicians can ensure your thermostat is working properly to maintain your desired comfort level.</li>
                  <li><b>Blower Motor Issues: </b>The blower motor pulls air through the furnace and distributes it throughout your home. If this component fails, you may experience reduced airflow or no airflow at all. Our furnace repair services include diagnosing and fixing blower motor problems to restore proper function.</li>
                  <li><b>Pilot Light or Ignition Problems: </b>Older models often rely on a pilot light, while newer units use electronic ignition. If your pilot light won't stay lit or your electronic ignition fails, your furnace won't produce heat. We can troubleshoot and repair these issues quickly.</li>
